Two people were arrested on Tuesday after they robbed a woman at a farm on Umlaas Road. Shaheen Suleiman of Magma Security and Investigation said the two men robbed a woman of firearms and other items that were in the house. “The armed response officers and the investigative team received a call about the farm attack after the suspects ran away. We responded to the call and two men in their 20s were arrested,” said Suleiman. He added three firearms and a substantial amount of ammunition were recovered. The two were detained at the Camperdown SAPS and are expected to appear in court soon.